history.content:
Which of the courses that satisfy the Human Contexts & Ethics requirement for the Data Science major also satisfy the Philosophy breadth requirement for L&S? (big plus if it is also offered in spring 2020 as well since I think PHILOS 121 is not)

I think the answer to this question was addressed in @9825 but some of the courses don't seem to satisfy the Philosophy breadth requirement anymore so I would appreciate if there were any updates on those courses.

    1. AMERSTD/AFRICAM C134. Information Technology and Society (4 units)
    2. BIO ENG 100. Ethics in Science and Engineering (3 units)
    3. CY PLAN 101. Introduction to Urban Data Analytics (4 units)
    4. DIG HUM 100. Theory and Method in the Digital Humanities (3 units)
    5. ESPM C167/PUB HLTH C160. Environmental Health and Development (4 units)
    6. HIST C184D / STS C104. Human Contexts and Ethics of Data (4 units)
    7. INFO 188. Beyond the Data: Humans and Values (3 units)
    8. ISF 100J. The Social Life of Computing (4 units)
    9. PHILOS 121. Moral Questions of Data Science (4 units)
history.subject: Philosophy Breadth + Data Science Human Contexts & Ethics
